  <tr valign="top">
    <td colspan="2" class="heading" >Ad Writing Tips</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="top">
    <td width="20" class="mattrlabeltext">
      1.</td>
    <td width="333">
      <span class="mattrlabeltext">Know your competition.</span> Before writing your ad, it
        always helps to read other similar ads currently running in the newspaper.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="top">
    <td width="20" class="mattrlabeltext">
      2.</td>
    <td width="333">
      <span class="mattrlabeltext">Be Clear. </span>Do not use abbreviations - not everyone
        knows what they mean.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="top">
    <td width="20" class="mattrlabeltext">
      3.</td>
    <td width="333">
      <span class="mattrlabeltext">Be specific.</span> The more information in your ad, the
        faster your item will sell.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="top">
    <td width="20" class="mattrlabeltext">
      4.</td>
    <td width="333">
      <span class="mattrlabeltext">Be unique.</span> How is your item(s) better/different
        than the other ads that will be running next to yours?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="top">
    <td width="20" class="mattrlabeltext">
      5.</td>
    <td width="333">
      <span class="mattrlabeltext">Use enhancements to stand out.</span> Bold type, &quot;Wow&quot; logo,
        border around your ad, etc. to make it easy for readers scanning the
        classifieds to see your ad before anyone else's.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="top">
    <td width="20" class="mattrlabeltext">
      6.</td>
    <td width="333">
      <span class="mattrlabeltext">Be sure to close the deal.</span> Include a price and a
        contact number. Even including a first name of who to call can help.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr valign="top">
    <td width="20" class="mattrlabeltext">
      7.</td>
    <td width="333">
      <span class="mattrlabeltext">Frequency Helps.</span> The more days the ad is in the
        newspaper, the faster the item(s) will sell and the better per line pricing
        you will receive.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
